race.comment: SORRENTO PALACE (6) didn't have much luck two back at Dubbo but was back in form last start, beaten narrowly over 1100m at Coonamble after racing up on the speed all the way. Draws the fence again and is cherry ripe after three runs back. Perfectly placed to go one better. TRUMPTY DUMPTY (11) has settled back in the field at his last couple of runs before launching big finishes, most recently getting up for fourth at Coonabarabran in a similar race to this. Just needs luck from a tricky draw to be right in contention. TURBULENT (7) turned in an eye-catcher over 1280m at Muswellbrook recently, closing hard to grab fifth in a BM66. Coming back in trip is a slight query at this stage of the prep but the blinkers back on should keep him sharp. SEVEN MILE MISSILE (2) can improve at the second run back from a year on the sidelines.
